</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uadaaeldarksmith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adaael Darksmith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/01 4:29:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What seems to be the power char on DAOC?</span><hr size=1> A cleric specing in spite is pretty powerful.  The nukes in the spite line are pretty good.  You basically can play a spite cleric like you'd play a wizard.  The nukes aren't quite as good...but you get to wear chain and you get to heal yourself between fights, and with your damage-add spell, you melee OK.  If you don't fully spec spite, you can bring rejuvenation up to where you get a zero-power instant cast heal every 15 minutes, which can let you take some extra tough mobs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uuggmopho.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uggmo Pho</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NT Action Hero </span><br>  Posts: 1363<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/01 12:52:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> Smite, not spite <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulyion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lyion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 383<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/01 7:45:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..</span><hr size=1> Right now Archers simply own. Scouts, Rangers, Hunters etc<br>
<br>
Most can solo easily, and we have a 42 Ranger that has soloed most of his way on Percival.<br>
<br>
They can kill most classes from long range and have stealth which means 90% of the classes out there cannot see them.<br>
<br>
I have seen rangers one shot kill dozens in a large battle without ever being in any danger.<br>
<br>
